# project:- Personal Voice Assistant :- Jarvis 

A Python-based personal voice assistant that can listen to voice commands and perform various tasks. 
The assistant uses speech recognition and text-to-speech to interact with the user in real time.

✨ Features
•Speech-to-text recognition
•Text-to-speech responses
•Executes common tasks (open apps, search online, tell time, etc.)
•User-friendly and customizable

🛠️ Tech Stack
•Language: Python
•Libraries: speech_recognition, pyttsx3, datetime, os, webbrowser (and more)

🚀 Future Improvements
•Add support for more advanced commands
•Integrate with APIs (weather, news, etc.)
•Build a GUI for better interaction



# Project:- AI Based Auto Responder (WhatsApp Bot)

🔹 Overview
This project is an AI-powered auto responder for WhatsApp built using Python. 
It is designed to automatically reply to incoming WhatsApp messages in real time with intelligent and context-aware responses. 
The bot reduces manual effort by handling repetitive queries, improving response time, and ensuring seamless communication


🔹 Features
✅ Automated Replies – Responds instantly to incoming last messages.
✅ AI-Powered – Generates smart, human-like responses using chatgpt .
✅ Custom Rules – Allows predefined rules for specific keywords or phrases.
✅ Real-Time Interaction – Works seamlessly with WhatsApp Web.
✅ Scalable – Can be extended for business use (customer support, FAQs, etc.).

•Tech Stack
Programming Language: Python 🐍
Libraries/Frameworks:
Selenium (for WhatsApp Web automation)

🔹 Future Enhancements

•Integration with advanced AI models (e.g., GPT-based).
•Support for multimedia (images, voice notes).
•Dashboard for monitoring conversations.
•Multi-user support for businesses.
